sequenceDiagram
    participant Orch as FMS Guardrails<br/>Orchestrator
    participant BuiltIn as Built-in Detector<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant HF as HuggingFace Detector<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Judge as LLM Judge Detector<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Model as Local Model<br/>(CPU/GPU)
    participant VLLM as vLLM Inference Server<br/>HTTP/HTTPS

    Note over Orch,VLLM: Flow 1: Built-in Text Content Detection (PII, File-type, Custom)

    Orch->>BuiltIn: POST /api/v1/text/contents<br/>HTTP :8080, No Auth
    Note over BuiltIn: Local processing:<br/>- Regex PII detection<br/>(email, CC, SSN, phone, IP)<br/>- File-type validation<br/>(JSON, XML, YAML + schema)<br/>- Custom Python functions<br/>(AST-sandboxed)
    BuiltIn-->>Orch: HTTP Response<br/>Detection results

    Note over Orch,VLLM: Flow 2: HuggingFace Model-based Content Detection

    Orch->>HF: POST /api/v1/text/contents<br/>HTTP :8000, No Auth
    HF->>Model: In-memory inference<br/>AutoModelForSequenceClassification<br/>or GraniteForCausalLM
    Model-->>HF: Classification result
    HF-->>Orch: HTTP Response<br/>Detection results

    Note over Orch,VLLM: Flow 3: LLM Judge Content Evaluation

    Orch->>Judge: POST /api/v1/text/contents<br/>HTTP :8000, No Auth<br/>Header: detector-id
    Judge->>VLLM: OpenAI-compatible API<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Configurable
    VLLM-->>Judge: LLM evaluation response
    Judge-->>Orch: HTTP Response<br/>Evaluation results<br/>(safety, toxicity, accuracy)
